<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/subtbiol.36.58977.figure1>
    dc:description "Figure 1. Comparison between species. Laoennea renouardi sp. nov. A-J holotype (NMBE 565863) K, L holotype and paratype shells of Laoennea carychioides Pa ́ ll-Gergely, A. Reischu ̈ tz & Maassen, 2020 (NHMW 113107). Scale bar: 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/475322" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/subtbiol.36.58977.figure3>
    dc:description "Figure 3. Speleological map and ecology of Tham Houey Ye (18 ° 56 ' 11 \" N, 102 ° 25 ' 28 \" E) including 11.2 km of caverns A shell of L. renouardi sp. nov. on moist substrate (image: M. Ferrand) and map of the cave showing the entrance to the cave, the collection site of L. renouardi sp. nov. marked by a red star and the entrance to the nearby touristic cave of Tham Pha Leusi. Tiny question marks on the map indicate uncertainties regarding the continuation of unexplored tiny galleries (EEGC et al. 2003, 2005) B landscape view from the entrance of Tham Houey Ye (image: M. Ferrand) C west gallery (image: M. Ferrand) D natural upper entrance of the cavern system Tham Houey Ye - Tham Pha Leusi (image: M. Ferrand) E active section of Ye River during the dry season in Tham Houey Ye (image: J- F. Fabriol)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/475324" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

